Button will give this white-space:nowrap. So I guess we need to set white-space:normal here.
And to make a long URL, and anything else (like a long id) wrap, then we also need to set word-break:break-all. I think this is best done maybe on the form tag on line 51.
Ideally, we should have a top level CSS (or SCSS) file to place some utility-type classes. If we don't want to do that in this PR, let's make an issue and add the styles inline here for the moment. You can do it inline like this:
<Form style={{
                // @ts-ignore
                'word-break': 'break-all'}}>
